414 to any fine imposed for a violation. The license of the host licensee may be revoked
425 or suspended and may be subject to the revocation or suspension of any other licenses
436 that the host licensee holds.'
4 Amend the bill by adding before the summary the following:
5 'Emergency clause. In view of the emergency cited in the preamble, this legislation
6 takes effect when approved.'
7 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
8 number to read consecutively.
9 SUMMARY
1100 This amendment replaces the bill and adds an emergency preamble and emergency
1111 clause. The amendment provides that if certain conditions are met, a licensed or unlicensed
1122 vendor may operate on the premises of an establishment licensed by the Department of
1133 Administrative and Financial Services, Bureau of Alcoholic Beverages and Lottery
1144 Operations and licensed by the Department of Health and Human Services or the
1155 Department of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry to prepare, serve, sell or offer for
1166 sale food.
1177 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
1188 (See attached)
